# Echo Codex — documentation map

**Echo Codex** is a free, open-source, mobile-first PWA — a template-driven renderer and tracker for tabletop RPG data. System-agnostic by design; D&D 5e at launch. No backend, local-first SQLite-on-OPFS storage.

## Where to look by task type

- **Designing or scoping a feature** → [`docs/spec.md`](../../docs/spec.md) (start with the matching numbered section).
- **Choosing between approaches** → [`docs/decisions/README.md`](../../docs/decisions/README.md), then existing ADRs.
- **Implementing a subsystem** → [`docs/architecture/`](../../docs/architecture/) (currently empty; plan-of-record is `spec.md` §6).
- **Pack authoring rules** → [`docs/spec.md`](../../docs/spec.md) §5 and §6.3, plus [`.cursor/rules/packs.mdc`](packs.mdc).
- **Agent conventions and non-negotiables** → [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md).
- **Open questions and prior exploration** → [`docs/notes/`](../../docs/notes/) (consult, but it is not load-bearing).
- **Full doc map with one-line summaries** → [`docs/INDEX.md`](../../docs/INDEX.md).

## Docs folder at a glance

- [`docs/INDEX.md`](../../docs/INDEX.md) — hand-curated map of every doc.
- [`docs/spec.md`](../../docs/spec.md) — canonical design spec (single source of truth).
- [`docs/decisions/`](../../docs/decisions/) — ADRs, immutable once accepted.
- [`docs/architecture/`](../../docs/architecture/) — living technical docs.
- [`docs/guides/`](../../docs/guides/) — task-oriented how-tos.
- [`docs/notes/`](../../docs/notes/) — agent-writable memory; observations, not commitments.

## Reminders

- **Never read or reintroduce ideas from `archive/`.** It is historical and superseded.
- Rules live in [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md); other rule files (`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`, `CLAUDE.md`, `.github/copilot-instructions.md`) are thin shims pointing back. Do not duplicate rules across them.
- When in doubt, read [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) first, then the relevant `docs/spec.md` section.
